“Lluvia de Peces (Fish Rain)”✨🌧️🐟 my washi tape design for 👻World Ghost Stories👻 collection @thewashistation!
.
15x10 mm | holographic foil
.
"Known as “The Lluvia de Peces” or “Rain of Fish,” it is said to occur at least once or twice in a year in Yoro, Honduras: during a massive rain storm, hundreds of small silver fish rain from the sky onto the streets of the small town.

Said to have been happening in the town since the 1800s in the months of May or June, each year a large storm rolls through the town with a very heavy rain, and once the storm has passed, the streets are found flapping and flopping, full of small, still-living fish."
.
#worldghoststories #thewashistation #honduranfolklore
